The course enables to produce cross-media project between Vikerraadio, ERR Novaator and social media. During the semester there will be a 1,5-hour radio broadcast "Huvitaja" on Vikerraadio, the articles and podcasts will be published on ERR Novaator, and the whole project will be extended to social media.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To create practical cross-media project as teamwork in cooperation with Estonian Public Broadcasting for their radio and digital platforms.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Student who has finished the course: -          knows the characteristics of radio, online and social media; -          is able to create a cross-media project taking into consideration the specifics of the medium; -          is able to prepare and produce diverse journalistic feature stories thet focus on sicence and research; -          manages to work effectively in team; -          is able to plan and operate teamwork; -          is able to reflect his/hers work independently and konws how to give constructive feedback to fellow students.
